  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7 and boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Peel and halve the <strong>potatoes</strong>, then add them to a pot of<strong> boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 10 min or until fork-tender</p>\n<p>Once done, drain, return them to the pot with the <strong>polenta</strong> and shake them until they're fluffy and fully coated</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2303Step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2303Step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2303Step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2303Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2303Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and chop the <strong>parsnips</strong> into batons</p>\n<p>Tip: Keep the parsnip tips thick to stop them from burning!</p>\n<p>Trim and halve the <strong>Chantenay carrots </strong>(no need to peel!)</p>\n<p>Trim the ends from the<strong> Brussels sprouts</strong></p>\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped carrots</strong> and <strong>parsnips</strong> (save the sprouts for later!) to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and set aside for later</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2303Step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2303Step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2303Step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2303Step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2303Step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>turkey joint</strong> to one side of a baking tray and top with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\n<p>Add the <strong>polenta coated potatoes</strong> to the other side of the tray with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up </p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2303Step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2303Step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2303Step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2303Step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2303Step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Put both trays in the oven for an initial 15 min or until the vegetables have caramelised and the potatoes are starting to brown</p>\n<p>Tip: Put the potatoes on the top shelf of your oven for extra crispiness!</p>\n<p>Whilst the turkey is in the oven, combine the <strong>honey</strong> and <strong>wholegrain mustard</strong> in a bowl – this is your <strong>honey mustard glaze</strong></p>\n<p>Re-boil a kettle</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 4,
